        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Silax cf. abdita, Galathea II stn. 716, from lot NHMD-868859. A, dorsal disc section, B, dorsal arm, C, central dorsal disc, D, dorsolateral arm, E, ventral aspect, F, jaws with madreporite, G, proximal ventral arm, H, dorsal disc, I, ventral aspect, J, dorsal arm, K, lateral proximal arm. A–G, SEM images, SMNH-189206, 189209, I–K, digital photos of dried speci- men, NHMD-868700. AdS, adoral shield, CPP, central primary plate, DAP, dorsal arm plate, IPa, infradental papillae, LAP, lateral arm plate, M, madreporite, OPa, oral papillae, OS, oral shield, VAP, ventral arm plate. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
